-- Instant view: Toyota posts big Q1 loss
-- 
-- Tue Aug 2, 2011 7:21am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/08/02/us-toyota-results-idUSTRE77113720110802

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp reported its first quarterly loss in two years as Japan's biggest earthquake hammered production and the yen's rise hit profitability on exports. 

 The world's biggest automaker made an operating loss of 108 billion yen ($1.4 billion) in the April-June quarter, compared with a profit of 211.7 billion yen a year ago. The result was better than the average loss estimate of 190 billion yen in a survey of six analysts by Thomson Reuters I/B/E/S. Following are reactions from fund managers and analysts: